<dl id="s19006av"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us19" href="#s19006av">Virtual: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s19all.htm#s19006av">sector 6(av)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. James the Less</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s19006av"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/lexn.htm#s19006av">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#s19006av">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#s19006av">1986 (12.1690)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/l22n.htm#s19006av">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s19006av">MS NLI.10-26</ms> </li><li><a name="n1J1d" href="../udra/u12da.htm#n1j1d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n1j1d.htm#s19006av">Draft: 12J.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>S. JAMES the Less</mark>, Apostle and Martyr, May 1. He was a relation of our Lord, and said to have borne such a strong resemblance to Him that it was this which made the kiss of Judas necessary. He was the first Bishop of Jerusalem, and suffered martyrdom from the Scribes and Pharisees, being thrown from a parapet of the temple, and finally slain with a fuller&apos;s club by one of the mob below. <small> E. A. Greene, <a name="EAGS" href="/udra/udex.htm#eags"><cite title="source">Saints and Their Symbols</cite></a> (1913), 107</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
